        "header": "3Method",
        "images": [
            {
                "img": "https://arxiv.org/html/2605.31577/2605.31577v1/x1.png",
                "caption": "Figure 3:SurGe architecture overview.SurGe combines a DINOv2[29]encoder with our Neighborhood Attention Decoder (NAD).\nNAD upsamples encoder features through a sequence of stagesℓ∈{1,…,5}\\ell\\in\\{1,\\ldots,5\\}, each built fromnℓn_{\\ell}NAD blocks.\nCompared to standard ViT[9]blocks, NAD blocks replace global self-attention with Neighborhood Attention[16], use window-matched RoPE[40]and only QK normalization[6]instead of pre-attention and pre-feedforward LayerNorm[1].",
                "position": 579
            }
        ]
    },
